<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;" class="faqpa">
<b>What is performance-based compensation?</b>
<% If page_section <> "ADA" Then %>
<br><img class="plresp" src="../images/clear.gif" width="10" height="1"  alt="" border="0"><br><a href="Javascript: vo_id();" onclick="playResponce(this);" class="ip">Play response</a>&nbsp;<a href="Javascript: vo_id();" onclick="playResponce(this);"><img style="margin: 0px 0px 0px 0px;" src="../images/video_off_faq.gif" alt="" border="0" align="absmiddle" class="pai" name="pa3"></a><span class="auraltext"><br class="alejandro_a3"></span>
<% Else %>
</p>
<p style="margin: 6px 0px 0px 0px;"><a name="answ3"></a>
Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America is committed to an environment where current individual performance is the key consideration in defining total compensation.<br>
Associates' pay is based on competitive market pay data and a robust performance management process.  Managers have tools for assessing performance and pay.  At Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America, top performers are compensated most aggressively for the role they are performing.
<br><br>
